summaries.short: Seth gets in trouble choosing between Summer and Anna.
summaries.full: When Seth tries to choose between dating Summer or Anna, he ends up in the middle of a very complicated situation. Meanwhile, Ryan visits his brother, Trey, in prison, accompanied by Marissa. When Julie finds out that Marissa is with Ryan in Chino, she becomes furious. As everyone nervously waits at the Cohen house for Ryan and Marissa to return, tensions mount, making the holiday a Thanksgiving to remember.

titles.full: Welcome To The OC, Bitches! Podcast Episode 11

summaries.short: Rachel and Melinda discuss “The Homecoming” (S1 Ep11) with their guest, Kelly Rowan, who played Kirsten Cohen on The OC.
summaries.full: Rachel and Melinda discuss “The Homecoming” (S1 Ep11) with their guest, Kelly Rowan, who played Kirsten Cohen on The OC. Find out who made Kelly laugh the most on set, her nickname for Rachel, and hear about Kelly's role in a Spielberg film! And of course, all about the Thanksgiving episode!

summaries.short: Anna and Summer are mad at Seth. Julie has love problems.
summaries.full: After Thanksgiving, Anna and Summer remain upset with Seth for his behavior on the holiday, and Seth struggles to reconcile with them. Meanwhile, Julie has relationship problems of her own. Jimmy and Sandy team up to tackle Jimmy's legal issues. A secret indiscretion by Kirsten is exposed. Ryan and Luke become partners on a history project, and an astonishing revelation creates an unexpected alliance between them.

summaries.short: Marissa and Ryan date. Summer denies her feelings for Seth.
summaries.full: Having seriously dated for one week, Marissa and Ryan are progressing slowly. Summer tries to deny her true feelings for Seth as she witnesses Anna and Seth getting closer. Meanwhile, the case against Kirsten's father, Caleb, continues to cause friction between Sandy and Kirsten. And Julie tries to mend her relationship with Marissa, inviting her, Jimmy and Ryan to attend her charity event--where her new relationship is revealed.

titles.short: Welcome To The OC, Bitches! PodcastE12
titles.full: Welcome To The OC, Bitches! Podcast Episode 12

summaries.short: Rachel and Melinda discuss “The Secret" (S1 Ep12) with their guest, Chris Carmack, who played Luke Ward on The OC.
summaries.full: Rachel and Melinda discuss “The Secret" (S1 Ep12) with their guest, Chris Carmack, who played Luke Ward on The OC. From "Nashville" to his band, Life on Eris, catch up on all things Carmack! And of course, the hosts talk memorable moments from "The Secret" like yogalates and the flossing scene. Chris also weighs in on the evolution of Luke from here on out.

summaries.short: The Cohens celebrate Chrismukkah. Seth juggles two girls.
summaries.full: Seth excitedly introduces a skeptical Ryan to Chrismukkah, a Cohen family tradition that resulted from Kirsten being Christian and Sandy being Jewish. As everyone prepares for a huge holiday party organized by Julie, Seth continues attempting to juggle Anna and Summer, both of whom want to date him exclusively. Meanwhile, on opposing sides of a lawsuit, Sandy and Kirsten dread working through the holiday season, but Kirsten learns something about her father that could change everything. And Ryan and Marissa's shopping trip leads to trouble--and the beginning of even bigger problems for Marissa.

titles.short: Welcome To The OC, Bitches! PodcastE10
titles.full: Welcome To The OC, Bitches! Podcast Episode 10

summaries.short: Rachel and Melinda discuss “The Perfect Couple” (S1 Ep10) with their guest, Bonnie Somerville, who played Rachel Hoffman on The OC.
summaries.full: Rachel and Melinda discuss “The Perfect Couple” (S1 Ep10) with their guest, Bonnie Somerville, who played Rachel Hoffman on The OC. The women talk second acts, their Zach Braff connection, sex scenes, and of course, the famous Chinese food seduction scene from this episode.

summaries.short: Summer is secretly jealous of Seth's relationship with Anna.
summaries.full: The summer is officially over, and it's the first day of school. Summer still ignores Seth in public, but privately she is jealous of Seth's burgeoning relationship with iconoclastic East Coast girl Anna Stern. And Summer isn't the only person fighting feelings of jealousy. Kirsten still isn't comfortable with Sandy's friendship with his sexy new co-worker, Rachel. Rachel makes matters worse when she specifically enlists Sandy to work on a lawsuit that an environmental group has initiated against Kirsten's father and his land development company, despite the obvious conflict of interest. Kirsten is incensed, but conflicted Sandy truly believes in the environmentalists' cause.

summaries.short: Rachel, Melinda, and their guest, Executive Producer and Writer on The OC, Stephanie Savage, discuss “The Best Chrismukkah Ever” (S1 Ep13).
summaries.full: Rachel, Melinda, and their guest, Executive Producer and Writer on The OC, Stephanie Savage, discuss “The Best Chrismukkah Ever” (S1 Ep13). This is the script that Stephanie said changed her life. Learn about what it was like going from producer to writer, who came up with Chrismukkah, and the episode line so good that it gave Rachel and Melinda the chills!

summaries.short: Kirsten's unruly sister hosts a huge New Year's Eve party.
summaries.full: Kirsten's rebellious 25-year-old sister, Hailey Nichol, comes to town on New Year's Eve, causing turmoil in the Cohen household. Ryan and Marissa plan a quiet evening of popcorn and movies at home, but Marissa later decides to attend a party hosted by a young man, Oliver Trask, who goes to the same therapist as she does. Meanwhile, Hailey persuades Sandy and Kirsten to go out so she can have a raging party in their house for a few friends. As the clock ticks closer to midnight, Ryan hopes that he can make it to Marissa in time for their first New Year's kiss together.

summaries.full: Rachel and Melinda discuss “The Heights” (S1 Ep9) with their guest, Patrick Norris, who directed this episode plus five more of The OC.

summaries.short: Ryan risks his future to keep Marissa from being sent away.
summaries.full: While Marissa recovers in the hospital from her overdose, everyone remains concerned about her. Julie vents her anger at Ryan, blaming him for all of Marissa's problems and warning him to stay away from her daughter. Meanwhile, Sandy tries to get acclimated to his new job at an affluent corporate law firm. Kirsten is displeased about her husband's rekindled relationship with his attractive former colleague, Rachel Hoffman, who is once again his co-worker--especially when Kirsten sees Sandy and Rachel having an intimate after-work cocktail. Dr. Michelle Kim, the dean of Harbor High School, is not happy about the prospect of having a student with a criminal background. She makes Ryan take a placement examination to determine whether or not he will be accepted into the school.

summaries.full: Rachel and Melinda discuss "The Rescue" (S1 Ep8) with their guest, Michael Lange, who directed this episode and several more of The OC. The hosts talk with “Uncle Mike” about chewing gum on set, crying on cue, and they dive into Julie Cooper's character in this emotional episode. They also take live fan calls for the first time!
